Body: I'm trying to access my smart kettle"
column11:
these ports are open:

23/tcp open telnet 80/tcp open http 2000/tcp open cisco-sccp

accessing port 23 with telnet was easy
column12:
now I'm searching for a tool to send hex messages to port 2000 to turn on/ shut down the device.

Is there a tool to send skinny protocol messages? And if not
column13:
how could I communicate with port 2000 over the command line?

Thanks in advance!

"
